 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Lost Ashes of War</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img src="/file/Elden-Ring/lost_ashes_of_war_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="lost ashes of war elden ring wiki guide 200px"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Affinity</td> 
     <td>None</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills">Skill</a></td> 
     <td>Used to duplicate <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Lost Ashes of War</strong>&nbsp;is an <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ash of War</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrade Materials" href="/Upgrade+Materials" target="">Upgrade Material</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>.&nbsp;<strong>Lost Ashes of War</strong> is a special item that can be exchanged to duplicate another Ash of War that you currently hold.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Empty ashes of war, devoid of any memories of battle.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Unable to apply any kind of affinity in their current state, but can be used by Smithing Master Hewg of the Roundtable Hold to recreate other ashes.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Thus does the copy pass into becoming the genuine article.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Lost Ashes of War Location in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Lost Ashes of War</strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>One can be purchased from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Isolated Merchant Weeping Peninsula" href="/Isolated+Merchant+Weeping+Peninsula">Isolated Merchant Weeping Peninsula</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<img title="runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;3000. He can be&nbsp;found in his shack at the very west of the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weeping Peninsula" href="/Weeping+Peninsula" target="">Weeping Peninsula</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=824&amp;lat=-214.9375&amp;lng=95.13315&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=824&amp;lat=-214.9375&amp;lng=95.13315&amp;zoom=8">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>One can be purchased from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Isolated Merchant Raya Lucaria" href="/Isolated+Merchant+Raya+Lucaria">Isolated Merchant Raya Lucaria</a>&nbsp;for <img title="runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;4000.&nbsp;From the Main Academy Gate site of grace, walk through the blue seal down the hill to the east, then south.</li> 
 <li>One can be found at the bottom of the water wheel lift on top of the cliff in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Raya Lucaria Academy" href="/Raya+Lucaria+Academy">Raya Lucaria Academy</a> near the Schoolhouse Classroom Site of Grace. (After riding the lift down, jump up the crystals to the west.)</li> 
 <li>One can be purchased&nbsp;from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hermit Merchant Ainsel River" href="/Hermit+Merchant+Ainsel+River">Hermit Merchant Ainsel River</a>&nbsp;for <img title="runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;3000. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1364&amp;lat=-127.74219&amp;lng=86.12628&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1364&amp;lat=-127.74219&amp;lng=86.12628&amp;zoom=8">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>Two can be purchased from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Isolated Merchant Dragonbarrow" href="/Isolated+Merchant+Dragonbarrow">Isolated Merchant Dragonbarrow</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<img title="runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;5,000 each. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive map?id=2353&amp;lat=-164.63125&amp;lng=136.080779&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+map?id=2353&amp;lat=-164.63125&amp;lng=136.080779&amp;zoom=8">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>Found in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sellia Hideaway" href="/Sellia+Hideaway">Sellia Hideaway</a>, at the bottom of the first large open cavern with giant purple crystals that the player traverses on. It will be on a corpse. Be wary of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Revenant" href="/Revenant">Revenant</a> down here guarding it and other items.&nbsp;[<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=10372&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=10372&amp;code=mapA">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ruin-Strewn Precipice" href="/Ruin-Strewn+Precipice" target="">Ruin-Strewn Precipice</a>: Within the area with 2 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Chanting Winged Dame" href="/Chanting+Winged+Dame">Chanting Winged Dames</a>. Look for the ledge behind the wooden platform. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring interactive map?id=6853&amp;lat=-104.734375&amp;lng=71.27019&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/interactive+map?id=6853&amp;lat=-104.734375&amp;lng=71.27019&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>One can be found in the first chest past <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skeletal Militiaman" href="/Skeletal+Militiaman">Skeletal Militiaman</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sage's Cave" href="/Sage's+Cave">Sage's Cave</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Altus Plateau" href="/Altus+Plateau">Altus Plateau</a>.</li> 
 <li>One can be found by the locked northwestern gate outside <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Leyndell, Royal Capital" href="/Leyndell,+Royal+Capital">Leyndell, Royal Capital</a>.&nbsp;[<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring interactive map?id=1188&amp;lat=-97.715625&amp;lng=107.396296&amp;zoom=8" href="/interactive+map?id=1188&amp;lat=-97.715625&amp;lng=107.396296&amp;zoom=8">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>One can be found in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Leyndell, Royal Capital" href="/Leyndell,+Royal+Capital">Leyndell</a>&nbsp;slums' sewer tunnels (not Subterranean Shunning-Grounds). Past some rats and small hand enemies, at the end of a long straight otherwise empty tunnel that has the Lost Ashes of War and a wall-clung <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fingercreeper" href="/Fingercreeper">Fingercreeper</a>&nbsp;enemy guarding it.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Subterranean Shunning-Grounds" href="/Subterranean+Shunning-Grounds" target="">Subterranean Shunning-Grounds</a>: One is found on a corpse outside&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dung Eater" href="/Dung+Eater" target="">Dung Eater</a>'s cell beneath the Royal Capital. Beware the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fingercreeper" href="/Fingercreeper">Fingercreeper</a>&nbsp;that emerges as you collect the item.&nbsp;[<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive map?id=4604&amp;lat=-101&amp;lng=115&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+map?id=4604&amp;lat=-101&amp;lng=115&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>One can be found on a corpse on the narrow ridge in the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mountaintops of The Giants" href="/Mountaintops+of+The+Giants">Mountaintops of The Giants</a>&nbsp;after the whip enemy. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive map?id=7402&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+map?id=7402&amp;code=mapA">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>One can be purchased from the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Imprisoned Merchant" href="/Imprisoned+Merchant" target="">Imprisoned Merchant</a>&nbsp;inside the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mohgwyn Dynasty Mausoleum" href="/Mohgwyn+Dynasty+Mausoleum" target="">Mohgwyn Dynasty Mausoleum</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;5,000. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive map?id=4663&amp;lat=-184.157812&amp;lng=147.893318&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB" href="/Interactive+map?id=4663&amp;lat=-184.157812&amp;lng=147.893318&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>One can be found on a corpse slumped over in front of a statue in&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Miquella's Haligtree" href="/Miquella's+Haligtree">Miquella's Haligtree</a>&nbsp;canopy. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4609&amp;lat=-44.86719&amp;lng=148.12295&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4609&amp;lat=-44.86719&amp;lng=148.12295&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/06r47EyKN08?t=685">Video Location</a></li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/HmVjDg4DksA?t=2870">Video Location</a> Leyndell</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Lost Ashes of War Elden Ring Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Lost Ashes of War</strong> can be used to duplicate <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>It&nbsp;does not provide any kind of affinity by itself.</li> 
 <li>Players need to take it to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Master Hewg" href="/Smithing+Master+Hewg" target="">Smithing Master Hewg</a> of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a> to duplicate other <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War">Ashes of War</a></li> 
</ul> 
